column4: High mountains coated with snow blocks. This was made to resemble the mountain range located in Central Europe.
A flat marsh biome of willow trees with green murky water.
The Bog consists of small Oak and Spruce scrubs, as well as Sweet Berry Bushes. Based on a Cranberry Bog.
A beautiful and wondrous biome containing lush-coloured grass with Pink and White Cherry Trees.
Gigantic fir tree forests with a cool temperature and dull colored grass.
Nether biome with crystals
Dying forest full of sparsely populated trees.
Jungles with Giant Glowshrooms and Oak bushes across the ground.
Beautiful Spruce Pear-Shaped trees make up this biome of green grass.
This biome consists of rough, high terrain with cobblestone boulders and lacks trees.
Twisting jade-coloured mountain cliffs covered with spruce trees, and spruce bushes.
Beautiful fields of lavender and jacaranda trees, with the occasional oak tree
Desert made of orange sand and flourishing, but messy trees. Unlike deserts, lush deserts have more vegetation.
A grassy biome with a few spruce trees and bushes scattered around.
Majestic grove of purple waters and beautiful enchanted trees. It is rare to find, though.
Dark Purple woods with a special sky and water colour. Several dangerous plants can spawn here. Beware
Formerly a sub-biome for the plains, it is now fields of large oak trees and bright grass.
A biome with light-colored grass and several trees scattered.
A lush biome with many flowering oak trees.
A forest of tall Redwood Trees and lots of ferns. This was made to resemble the Redwood Forests in Northern California.
Forests of tall birch and oak trees with different colored autumn leaves.
Dry Grassland with mixed Acacia and Spruce scrubs
A relatively flat biome with oak shrubs and many allium flowers.
A rare swampy biome with many patches of cobwebs on ground and trees. The foliage shows its dark, dull color
Snowy variant of the Coniferous Forest biome.
A snowless wasteland of shrubs and cobblestone.
A hazy biome with pools of murky brown water. Dead trees also appear in this biome. It is an inhospitable place, and not recommended for beginners.
Lush swamps with a deep blue water color and willow trees
A beach made entirely of gravel, mainly spawns adjacent to Woodland or other temperate biomes
Where it all started: A perfect replica of the original Minecraft Classic, including roses which were removed in vanilla 1.7.
A beautiful, but extremely rare island biome with Rainbow Birch Trees all over the place.
A rare island biome with palm trees and bright blue skies. Sub-biome of the Ocean.

A desolate biome with lots of lava. This biome used to generate in large areas, but can only be found as a rare ocean sub-biome island in later versions. It is dangerous, note the lava and steep incline.
A nether biome that contains bone columns and flesh tendons.
A vast expanse of flat terrain with tulips on almost every piece of ground. Replaced with Flower Meadow in 1.13.2.
Grass and sand
Nether Biome, some trees
Nether biome.  Blackstone and obsidian ground
Dried salt ground, sparse dried trees.  Brownish water
Similar to a taiga with fewer trees
Some shorter redwood trees
White sand, blue waters
Nether biome? Ash ground, small shrubs, one-high trees
A field dedicated to Allium flowers scattered with Red Oaks.  Lush overworld biome with some lakes and red oaks.  Relatively rare usually.  Warm climate
A snow covered mountain inspired by the Alps found in Europe.  Icy mountainous overworld biome with lots of snow.  Surrounded by alpine foothills
A field dedicated to the Amaranth flowers scattered with Jacaranda Trees.  Lush plainslike overworld biome with some lakes and jacaranda forests. Normally rare
An old forest filled with massive ancient trees.  Magical and usually rare.  May have flowering/glowing ancient forest as a subiome.
Desert forest biome in the overworld.  Somewhat rare normally.
Forests inspired by the Aspen trees found in Utah and around the world.
An open space scattered with pumpkins.  A cool, dry, plains in the overworld.  May have Cika Woods around it.
A dry desert/savanna with sparse vegetation.  Based on the Baobab trees found in Africa and Australia.
A dense swamp filled with Willow Trees and inspired by the Bayous found in the Gulf Coast region of the United States.
A taiga with Blue Spruce trees.  A cool, coniferous forest in the overworld.  May have hills.
A mountainous biome inspired by the Bluff Mountains in Tennessee.  A cool mountainous biome with coniferous trees.
A biome inspired by real world Boreal Forests from around the world.  Top blocks are peat and grass.
Tall plateaus broken by steep, sheer cliff faces.  Does not spawn by default. Warm grassy climate.
A warm overworld forest inspired by the Cherry Blossom forests in Japan.  Similar to the Biomes O'Plenty version, there are two types of trees.
A cold coniferous forest, the first ever biome created in BYG.  Top blocks are podzol, grass, and coarse dirt.
A brown and murky swamp found in colder climates around the world.
Another similar biome to Biomes O'Plenty.  Cold forest inspired by coniferous forests from around the world.
An elevated rare and magical rocky biome found in warmer climates with an abundance of Rainbow Eucalyptus Trees.
Swamp inspired by the Giant Cypress Swamp found in southern Delaware.
A thick fog covers this area where nothing grows.  Top blocks are black sand. Somewhat rare ocean biome with a desert climate.  Spooky wasteland.
A warm overworld forest inspired by the many deciduous forests found around the world.
A unique biome inspired by the White Cliffs of Dover in England filled with Dacite.  A cold coniferous mountain biome.  The top blocks are overgrown dacite, podzol, and more dacite.
A hilly desert inspired from areas around the world.
A lush and dense forest filled with Ebony trees and bushes inspired from their native land of India.
A warm magical fantasy forest with glowing leaves.  Typically rare.
An evergreen forest filled with Holly trees like those found in Massachusetts.  An icy coniferous forest.
A rare magical mutation of the Bayou filled with Glowshrooms.
A warm plains biome similar to Biome O'Plenty's Highlands.  An elevated and relatively flat plateau scattered with trees and covered in grass.
A vast lake scattered with islands inspired by the Great Lakes found in the northern United States and Canada.
An elevated jungle based off the Guiana Shield found in South America.
A jungle filled with Indigo and Pink Jacaranda trees with occasional bamboo.
A lush, icy plainslike biome with frozen lakes.
Swamp inspired by the several mangrove swamps on shores found across the world.
A taiga filled with Maple trees like those found in the northeastern United States and southeastern Canada.
A vibrant green meadow.
Based off the Mojave Desert found in the American Southwest, this biome is home to the Joshua Tree.  A hot, dry, sandy biome.
A forest filled with apple orchard trees.
A prairie biome like those founds in the Mississippi River valley.
A desert full of red sand inspired by the red desert in Wyoming.  Red sand is great for Botania hourglasses too, y'know, but some people just hate pretty, functional flowers.  =(
An oak forest with red oaks.
A mountainous desert biome inspired by the Red Rock Mountains/Canyon outside Las Vegas, Nevada.
A dense forest inspired by the unique Redwood trees founds in California.  Normally rarely spawns.
A plain covered with rose bushes and other red flowers.  A warm, lush plains biome.  Typically fairly rare.
A colorful birch forest that feels like autumn.
A colorful deciduous forest that feels like autumn.
A colorful oak forest that feels like autumn.
A colorful taiga forest that feels like autumn with a mix of Aspen and Pine.
An interesting biome to find black ice.  Rare, snowy, icy biome.
Similar to Biomes O'Plenty's version, it is a dry desertlike plains with sparse trees.  The top blocks are a mix of teracotta, grass, and coarse dirt.  Based off the Sierra Nevada Mountains.
A dry, hot desert based off the Sierra Nevada Mountains.
An interesting elevated fantasy biome with trees that somehow resemble Acaciasâ€¦ a mutation? Who knows.  An extreme hills biome.
A snowy variant of the Blue Taiga.
A snowy variant of the Coniferous Forest.
A snowy variant of the Deciduous Forest.
A snowy taiga with evergreens.
A warm, dense overworld biome with tall plateaus.
Biome inspired by the dense Black Forest found in Germany filled with Pine and scattered with Aspen and conifers.  Top blocks are peat, coarse dirt, and grass.
A mutated variant of the Tropical Rainforest overgrown with fungi.  A warm, dense magical jungle.
A biome inspired by tropical rainforests from around the world.  Magical.
A cold magical wasteland.  Somewhat rare normally.  Top blocks are peat and grass.
A vibrant swamp that feels full of life.
People say they hear the screams of witches who were killed in Salem, some even claim to have seen witches through its dense fog wandering these woods...
A rather dense forest with big bushy trees.  This one is also magical.
Uniquely shaped Zelkovas live on this land in high numbers.
